Glenn Branca October 1948 May 2018 was American avantgarde composer and guitarist known for his use volume alternative guitar tunings repetition droning and the harmonic series Branca received 2009 Foundation for Contemporary Arts Grants Artists Award Born Harrisburg Pennsylvania Branca started playing the guitar age also created number tape sound art collage pieces for his own amusement After attending York College 19661967 started the shortlived cover band The Crystal Ship with Whiteside and Dave Speece the summer 1967 the early 1970s Branca studied theater Emerson College Boston 1973 moved from Boston London with his then girlfriend Meg English After moving back Boston 1974 met John Rehberger While there began experimenting with sound the founder experimental theater group called Bastard Theatre 1975 Working out loft Massachusetts Avenue they wrote and produced the musictheater piece Anthropophagoi for twoweek run 1976 The Bastard Theatres second production was What Actually Happened new loft Central Square Cambridge and later The Boston Arts Group Considering the unconventional and sometimes confrontational nature the productions the shows still received interested reviews from the Phoenix and The Boston Globe All music for Bastard Theatre productions were original compositions Branca Rehberger and were performed live the actormusicians 1976 Branca moved New York City continue experimental theater encountered the Dodo Band and watched their rehearsals Chelsea hoping use the space for theater production Branca spent time with one its members Jeffrey Lohn who introduced him bands such Suicide The two began forming theater group when Branca decided wanted form band which called the Static and later Theoretical Girls Branca put posters recruit members and after seeing one the posters Lohn expressed interest Lohns girlfriend Margaret Wys joined the band its bassist and they borrowed drummer Mike Anthol from the Dodo Band Artist Dan Graham booked the band Franklin Furnace for its first performance The group reformed 1977 with Wharton Tiers its drummer Branca also recorded Barbara Esss band Pants for their debut release Records and performed with Rhys Chathams Guitar Trio 1977 noise music experience that was very important the development his compositional voice Branca 1979 1982 Branca launched his own record label Neutral Records releasing Pants and the first few records New York noise rockers Sonic Youth the early 1980s released his first album under his own name Lesson the same year composed several mediumlength compositions for electric guitar ensembles including The Ascension 1981 and Indeterminate Activity Resultant Masses 1981 The Ascension appeared his second same titled solo album 1981 Indeterminate Activity Resultant Masses wasnt released until 2008 Soon after these two compositions began composing symphonies for orchestras electric guitars and percussion which blended droning industrial cacophony and microtonality with quasimysticism and advanced mathematics 1982 worked with ZEV for Brancas Symphony which ZEV had solo segment swinging with metal can overhead and rattling chains and sheets steel With Symphony Gloria 1983 began systematically compose for the harmonic series which considered the structure underlying not only all music but most human endeavors this project Branca was initially influenced the writings Dane Rudhyar Hermann von Helmholtz and Harry Partch Early members his group included Thurston Moore and Lee Ranaldo Sonic Youth Page Hamilton Helmet Phil Kline The DelByzanteens and several members Swans including Michael Gira Dan Braun and Algis Kizys further develop his compositions based the harmonic series Branca built several electrically amplified instruments his own invention expanding his ensemble beyond the guitar few these instruments were third bridge zithers called harmonic guitars also built instruments with many strings which referred mallet guitars because they were percussion instruments played with drumsticks and monotone electric cymbaloms with additional third bridge resonating positions Many these instruments can seen the live performances that appeared the DVD Glenn Branca Symphonies Live The Kitchen the early 1990s David Baratier attempted document Brancas teaching style They Walked Line September 1996 The Glenn Branca Ensemble played the opening ceremony for the Aarhus Festival Denmark The ceremony took place the Musikhuset Opera House and the audience were the Queen Denmark the mayor Aarhus and other dignitaries After the composer received more than major commissions starting 1981 until the time his death 2018 Brancas music has started receive academic attention Some scholars most prominently Kyle Gann consider him and Rhys Chatham member the totalist school postminimalism Beginning with Symphony Branca began composing for traditional orchestra although never abandoned the electric guitar Branca also played duets for excessively amplified guitars with his wife Reg Bloor and conducted his 13th symphony for 100 electric guitars the base the World Trade Center New York City June 2001 less than three months before the centers destruction the September attacks Since that time his 100 guitar piece has been performed cities all over the and Europe 2008 wrote his 14th Symphony entitled The Harmonic Series which performed traditional orchestra The first movement this symphony named 2000000000 Light Years From Home premiered Louis performed the Louis Symphony Orchestra conducted David Robertson November 2008 This was the 12th major orchestra perform Brancas orchestral work since 1986 2008 was awarded grant from the Foundation for Contemporary Arts Grants Artists Award well CAPS grant 1983 award from the National Endowment for the Arts 1988 and NYSCA grant 1998 all for music composition 2010 Fortissimo Records rereleased Brancas 1981 album The Ascension special edition 180grams vinyl and Branca wrote piece The Ascension The Sequel which was released the same year the label Systems Neutralizers This follow piece led new interest his work and notable performances Primavera Sound Festival 2011 and Villette Sonique 2011 October 2014 Branca premiered Ascension Three touring with Glenn Branca Ensemble Europe February 2015 Brancas second 100 electric guitars piece Symphony Orgasm was premiered Cit Musique Paris The Light for David for four guitars bass and drums premiered October 2016 the Roulette Brooklyn May 2018 Reg Bloors official Facebook page revealed post that Branca had died from throat cancer the night before was 